# Generic Tool Setup Guide (Project Initiation)

Use this guide during project initiation to intentionally configure your communication, documentation, and collaboration tools. These questions help you design a setup that supports clarity, accessibility, and smooth execution — regardless of whether your team uses Google Workspace, Microsoft 365, ClickUp, Jira, or a hybrid environment.

---

## 1. Communication Setup (Email, Chat, Messaging)

### Key Questions
- What channels will we use for decisions vs. FYIs?
- Do we need project‑specific signatures or templates?
- What filters, labels, or rules help reduce noise?
- How will we support asynchronous contributors?
- What expectations do we need to set (response times, availability, escalation)?

### Outputs
- Email signatures  
- Templates for recurring messages  
- Filters/labels/rules  
- Communication norms documented in the Communication Plan  

---

## 2. Calendar & Scheduling Setup

### Key Questions
- What is our meeting cadence (weekly, biweekly, monthly)?
- Do we need shared calendars for milestones or releases?
- What is our rule for scheduling across time zones?
- What meetings require agendas sent in advance?
- What meetings require notes or decisions logged afterward?

### Outputs
- Shared calendars  
- Meeting templates  
- Scheduling norms  
- Time‑zone rules  

---

## 3. File & Document Management (Drive, OneDrive, SharePoint)

### Key Questions
- What folder structure supports our deliverables?
- What naming conventions prevent confusion later?
- Which documents need version control?
- Which documents should be read‑only?
- Who needs edit vs. view access?
- How will we store final vs. working drafts?

### Outputs
- Folder structure  
- Naming conventions  
- Permissions  
- Versioning rules  
- “Final vs. Working” guidelines  

---

## 4. Collaboration Tools (Docs, Sheets, Word, Excel, ClickUp, Jira)

### Key Questions
- Which documents need templates?
- Which documents need shared editing?
- Which documents need approval workflows?
- What dashboards or boards do we need?
- What fields, labels, or components support clarity?

### Outputs
- Document templates  
- Shared editing rules  
- Approval workflows  
- Boards/dashboards  
- Labels/components  

---

## 5. Accessibility & Inclusiveness

### Key Questions
- Do we provide multiple ways to participate (async, sync, written, verbal)?
- Are documents readable and accessible (contrast, formatting, plain language)?
- Do we share materials in advance for reflective thinkers?
- Do we summarize decisions in writing for clarity?

### Outputs
- Accessibility guidelines  
- Participation pathways  
- Document formatting standards  

---

## 6. Project‑Specific Automations (Optional)

### Key Questions
- What notifications or alerts help prevent delays?
- What automations reduce repetitive work?
- What integrations support visibility (email → board, form → tracker)?

### Outputs
- Filters  
- Rules  
- Automations  
- Integrations  

---

## 7. Final Review

- Tools support the Communication Plan  
- Tools support the RACI Matrix  
- Tools support the Stakeholder Register  
- Setup is documented and repeatable  
- Nothing depends on a single person’s inbox or drive  
